I"â<h1 id="the-liquibaseproperties-configuration-file">The liquibase.properties configuration file</h1>

<p>Liquibase can read paramaters for its execution from standard Java Property files. A simple liquibase.properties file would look like this:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>driver: oracle.jdbc.OracleDriver
classpath: ../ojdbc14.jar
url: jdbc:oracle:thin:@localhost:1521:XE
username: tbd
password: tbd
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Note that paths are relative to the current directory.</p>

<p>For each property defined in the file that matches a property in the goal being invoked that property of the goal will be set.</p>

